{"key":"processedPost-17997128","value":{"id":17997128,"first":17996027,"last":18002247,"when":1364012039,"utime":"03/23/13 07:13 AM","cleanedPost":"Oven drying can ruin them.&nbsp; When using a dehydrator they dry much faster and the actives seem to be preserved better.<br />Yes, I've grilled them too.&nbsp; Prepared properly, cubensis is a gourmet edible.&nbsp; Some of the actives are destroyed by the grill but that's a good thing when eating a meal. <img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"https://files.shroomery.org/smileys/wink.gif\" alt=\":wink:\" title=\":wink:\"/><br />You can boil them in water to make tea with very little degradation, but that same temperature in dry heat nukes them pretty bad.&nbsp; It's best to fan dry only, and then use desiccant.<br />RR"}}